      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): support Streamable HTTP MCP transport on loopback server",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- The MCP loopback HTTP server (`mcp-http.request.ts`) rejects GET requests with 405, but the MCP config it generates specifies `\"type\": \"http\"` (Streamable HTTP transport)\n- Claude Code's Streamable HTTP client sends GET to `/mcp` to open an SSE notification channel as part of initialization\n- The 405 response causes Claude Code to hang at \"still connecting\" indefinitely, leaving the agent without any OpenClaw MCP tools for the entire session\n- Added GET/SSE support (idle stream, auth-gated), DELETE for session teardown, and `Mcp-Session-Id` header on POST responses per the Streamable HTTP spec\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] Verify GET `/mcp` with valid bearer returns 200 + `text/event-stream`\n- [ ] Verify GET `/mcp` without auth returns 401\n- [ ] Verify DELETE `/mcp` returns 200\n- [ ] Verify POST `/mcp` responses include `Mcp-Session-Id` header\n- [ ] Verify unsupported methods still return 405\n- [ ] End-to-end: Claude Code session connects to OpenClaw MCP tools without \"still connecting\"",
        "branch": "fix/mcp-streamable-http",
